# DSP — Register New Files

When creating a new source file in this project, register it in DSP.

## For a New Module or Class

```bash
dsp-cli create-object --source <file-path> --purpose "<what this module does>"
```

## For a New Standalone Function

```bash
dsp-cli create-function --source <file-path> --purpose "<what this function does>" --owner <parent-uid>
```

Find the parent UID:

```bash
dsp-cli find-by-source <parent-directory-or-file>
```

## After Registration

1. Add imports for any dependencies this file uses:

```bash
dsp-cli add-import <new-uid> <dependency-uid> --why "<reason>"
```

2. If the file exposes a public API consumed by other modules:

```bash
dsp-cli create-shared <new-uid> <export-name>
```

## When to Skip

Do not register:
- Test files (unless they represent a test architecture module)
- Config files (.env, tsconfig.json, etc.)
- Generated files (compiled output, lock files)
- One-off scripts not part of the application architecture
